schema: proofloop-spec-driven

context:
  project: "<project-name>"
  description: "<project-description>"

rules:
  - Every Brain-dispatched task must have verifiable acceptance criteria.
  - Direct Task uses Brain -> general -> Completion Receipt -> Brain self-check.
  - OpenSpec Change uses Propose -> Planning Contract Verifier -> Executor -> Code Verifier per slice -> Implementation Reviewer -> Archive.
  - OpenSpec canonical skills remain untouched; ProofLoop applies an overlay through agents and contracts.
  - CodeGraph is a tool protocol, not a default agent.
  - Committer records task-diff-snapshot after tasks and commits slice-output only after verifier PASS.
  - High-risk work uses Required Review Skills, not P2 flow.
